h1. create-unit-test-service-spock

h2. Purpose

The @create-unit-test-service-spock@ generates all the unit tests for a service with the "Spock Framework":https://code.google.com/p/spock/

h2. Examples

{code:java}
grails create-unit-test-service-spock Person
grails create-unit-test-service-spock "*"
{code}

h2. Description

Given at least one domain class, this command creates unit tests for a service with the "Spock Framework":https://code.google.com/p/spock/ . The command will generate the following files:
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ServiceListSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ServiceListMaxSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ServiceListOffsetSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ServiceListSortOrderSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ServiceCreateSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ServiceUpdateSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ServiceGetSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ServiceDeleteSpec.groovy@

Usage:

{code:java}
grails create-unit-test-service-spock [domainClass]
{code}

Arguments:
* @domainClass@ - Either a domain class name (case-sensitive) without its package or a wildcard (*). If you specify the wildcard the artifacts will be generated for all domain classes.

